comments: This is a rare opportunity to learn many new things about the history/archaeology of medieval Ireland. Prof. FitzPatrick's style of teaching is very erudite and smooth and you will have a tremendous amount of fun even if you're not particularly interested in archaeology--you will soon be won over by Prof. FitzPatrick's own enthusiasm! She is also very respectful of her students and provides as much individual help and attention as needed and/or requested for.
